PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1784758688
OL,3,CSpain temperatures to surpass 44C as
OL,4,Cwildfires burn across Europe
OL,6,FFirefighters were called out 30 times
OL,7,Fto a fire in Vibo Valentia, southern
OL,8,FItaly, which continues to burn.
OL,10,FEurope is the world's fastest warming
OL,11,Fcontinent according a report by the
OL,12,FUN's World Meteorological Organisation
OL,13,Fand the European Union's climate
OL,14,Fagency, Copernicus.
OL,16,FMore than 10,000 deaths across Europe
OL,17,Fcould be attributed to the late June
OL,18,Fheatwave, figures from mortality
OL,19,Fmonitoring service EuroMOMO suggest.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
